{
  "stem": "12462.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was there kind of on tenterhooks, because the Nazis obviously didn't like it, but they didn't want to be in a position of excluding him, because of his connections, I think, to the But I did not speak to any Jewish people at that time in Germany.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I spoke to many of them later in Poland, but that's another story.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I had made my conclusions up long before I got there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I was at the University of Wisconsin, I wrote a long paper on which I got an A-plus-plus, called 'The Structure of National Socialism.' And I submitted this to one of my professors.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he thought it was quite outstanding.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, that was one reason I had received a fellowship to the University of Chicago.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I turned that fellowship down in order to go to London, because several professors told me you ought to get out of the country for a year and study.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so I did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And since I could afford it, I went to study on my own.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, obviously, there was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a regime of oppression, where people were thrown into concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was known in America among scholarly circles and among many other people, for that matter, and that there was a persecution of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The boycott of the Jews in 1933, in April, was well known, the German boycott, the Nazi boycott.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went to England already convinced that the Nazis were a very evil force and that I would always be opposed to them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And nothing I learned in London, I can assure you, changed my mind.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When you went back stateside, what did you do after the University of London?",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
